The Citation for the Award of the Military Cross to 2nd Lt, Basil Green N. Staff. Regt is published in the Supplement to the London Gazette of 24 August 1917:  For the trench raid of 14 Jun 1917.

&quot;For conspicuous gallantry and devotion to duty.  He led a raid with great dash into the enemy trenches, after which he pentrated into cellars and dug-outs on the far side of the trench, inflicting further casualties.  Later he went out into &quot;No-Man's Land&quot; with one man, and spent an hour searching for wounded near the enemy's wire, setting a splendid example of courage to his men.&quot;

There is implicit evidence that 2Lt Basil Green led soldiers trained as Scouts, the forebears of a Reconnaissance Platoon, in 1/5 North Staffordshire.//
